WEBVTT

00:05.630 --> 00:07.621
CLARK:
Lois, we're going against traffic.

00:07.799 --> 00:09.710
Sort of the point here. Try and keep up.

00:09.884 --> 00:12.591
-These glasses are driving me crazy.
-So you've said.

00:12.762 --> 00:14.753
And this jacket, it's not helping.

00:14.931 --> 00:18.890
You chose to take his hero game public.
Either the Blur starts wearing a mask or--

00:19.060 --> 00:20.721
Clark Kent does. I know.

00:20.895 --> 00:22.760
Your words, not mine.

00:23.064 --> 00:27.057
After all the hero hating of the VRA,
if the Blur doesn't show his face soon...

00:27.277 --> 00:30.064
...people are gonna stop
trusting me again.

00:30.488 --> 00:33.821
That didn't stop the mayor from offering
the Blur the key to the City.

00:33.992 --> 00:36.699
-Yeah, but that's--
-Before that hero face ends up...

00:36.870 --> 00:39.703
...on Jumbotron screens
in all your red-and-blue glory...

00:39.873 --> 00:44.082
...we need to make sure there is nothing
handsome or heroic about Clark Kent.

00:44.294 --> 00:45.579
And that's supposed to help?

00:46.004 --> 00:47.414
Yes.

00:47.589 --> 00:50.877
So just-- I don't know.
Slope your shoulders a little bit...

00:51.051 --> 00:54.088
...speak a little softer
and stop being so....

00:54.888 --> 00:57.300
-What?
-Great.

00:58.308 --> 01:01.471
Honey, you need to be invisible
and forgettable and....

01:04.064 --> 01:05.600
Exactly like that.

01:07.358 --> 01:08.734
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

01:17.202 --> 01:18.282
What is it?

01:18.453 --> 01:23.368
Lois, l was like that, in Smallville.
The thought of going back to that, l....

01:23.541 --> 01:26.908
Clark, the real you can burn holes
through buildings with a look...

01:27.087 --> 01:29.874
...and lift a freight train with one finger.
Get over it.

01:30.757 --> 01:33.965
Last thing you should worry about
is teaching me Mild-Mannered 101.

01:34.135 --> 01:37.719
Focus on that promotion now that
Steve Lombard went to Daily Star.

01:37.889 --> 01:41.381
-They said that desk could be yours.
-l'm counting on it.

01:44.854 --> 01:45.969
These need to stay on.

01:51.111 --> 01:52.772
Just work on it.

01:55.615 --> 01:58.027
[TEENAGERS CHATTERING]

01:59.244 --> 02:02.361
Hey, guys. Wait. Guy--

02:04.332 --> 02:05.617
[GRUNTS]

02:05.792 --> 02:07.657
[TIRES SCREECH]

02:13.591 --> 02:15.331
[CRASHES]

02:24.227 --> 02:25.842
MAN 1:
He hit him at 40 miles an hour.

02:26.020 --> 02:28.397
WOMAN: Did you see that?
MAN 2: Did you see that?

02:28.565 --> 02:29.930
[CROWD CLAMORING]

02:30.108 --> 02:32.645
WOMAN:
That was so amazing.

02:42.620 --> 02:45.236
SKEETS [OVER EAR PIECE]: Brilliant save.
-Of course it was, Skeets.

02:45.415 --> 02:46.700
Say "cheese," junior.

02:46.916 --> 02:48.417
Cheese.

02:50.837 --> 02:52.452
Life lesson to remember, kid:

02:52.630 --> 02:55.121
Always keep yourself open
to the cameras.

02:55.300 --> 02:57.256
Who are you?

02:58.761 --> 03:00.922
I'm sure you're all wondering
who I am.

03:01.097 --> 03:03.554
Well, how about the 411?

03:03.725 --> 03:06.762
I'm pure gold, ladies and gentlemen.

03:06.936 --> 03:11.305
I am Booster Gold, the greatest hero
you've never heard of...

03:11.482 --> 03:13.347
...till now.

03:13.526 --> 03:15.562
[CROWD CLAPPING]

03:16.946 --> 03:20.359
Later today, at the Ace of Clubs,
I'll be signing autographs.

03:20.533 --> 03:21.739
Stop on by.

03:21.951 --> 03:24.363
WOMAN:
l'll so be there.

03:34.380 --> 03:36.462
If you need a hero...

03:36.966 --> 03:38.672
...ping me.

03:45.350 --> 03:47.306
Nice glasses.

03:48.978 --> 03:50.559
Remember...

03:50.730 --> 03:54.268
...it's Booster Gold!

04:53.042 --> 04:55.704
He said, "Nice glasses,"
like he knew who I really was.

04:55.878 --> 05:00.212
Maybe he just liked your glasses. Or not.
You're sure you'd never seen him before?

05:00.383 --> 05:03.716
How could you miss that? Booster Gold
didn't come here for no reason.

05:03.886 --> 05:06.218
I need to figure out who he is
and why he's here.

05:06.389 --> 05:09.552
Hey, hey, watch it.
When did you forget how to walk, Kent?

05:09.726 --> 05:11.262
-Sorry.
-Clark.

05:11.436 --> 05:13.722
Just excuse him. Heh.

05:14.230 --> 05:15.310
I'm trying to help.

05:15.523 --> 05:17.889
Help? By making me stumble
into Ron Troupe?

05:18.067 --> 05:21.935
Yeah, it's a start. Clark, you want people
to look down on Clark Kent...

05:22.113 --> 05:24.320
...so they can look up to the Blur.

05:24.532 --> 05:26.648
Which isn't exactly gonna
be a fitting name...

05:26.826 --> 05:30.239
...after you stop blurring
and start standing in the spotlight.

05:30.413 --> 05:33.621
Well, the spotlight's kind of crowded
with Booster Gold.

05:33.958 --> 05:37.621
Okay, not that my curiosity
isn't in overdrive about Booster boy...

05:37.795 --> 05:42.084
...but you are making way more
out of this than you need to. Okay?

05:42.258 --> 05:43.293
Okay.

05:43.468 --> 05:48.428
I'm sure our flying car salesman
will buzz off as fast as he buzzed in.

05:48.973 --> 05:51.464
WOMAN 1:
Oh, my God.

05:51.642 --> 05:53.928
[CROWD CHATTERING]

05:55.188 --> 05:57.179
WOMAN 2:
Hold it right there.

05:57.690 --> 06:00.807
WOMAN 3:
Here's my number. Call me.

06:03.654 --> 06:07.317
Either one's fine.
I don't really have a bad side, guys. Heh.

06:07.492 --> 06:09.107
You're sitting at my desk.

06:09.285 --> 06:10.365
Yeah, I can read.

06:10.578 --> 06:15.789
So where is the greatest reporter
that this city has ever known?

06:15.958 --> 06:20.122
-All right, everybody, back to work.
-There you are, the hero maker.

06:20.463 --> 06:21.794
Excuse me.

06:21.964 --> 06:24.296
Lois Lane. Booster Gold.

06:26.844 --> 06:28.300
What can I do for you?

06:28.471 --> 06:29.881
We're gonna help each other...

06:30.098 --> 06:34.137
...because one exclusive interview
with the gold guardian of Metropolis...

06:34.310 --> 06:37.643
...and you're gonna lock up
that promotion that you're up for.

06:38.147 --> 06:40.138
It's a Booster Gold guarantee.

06:41.609 --> 06:44.146
How did you know I was up for a...?

06:44.320 --> 06:45.821
Never mind.

06:45.988 --> 06:48.730
I'm not interested in you
and neither is the Daily Planet.

06:48.908 --> 06:53.197
Why don't you see if you can fit that big
old head of yours through the exit door?

06:53.538 --> 06:54.823
SKEETS:
Sir?

06:54.997 --> 06:56.578
My agent.

06:56.749 --> 06:59.536
You're going to be late for the signing.

06:59.836 --> 07:03.670
Excuse me, folks, but duty calls.

07:04.048 --> 07:06.835
We should do lunch soon.

07:09.887 --> 07:11.923
CAT: Booster.
BOOSTER: See you later, pumpkin.

07:12.140 --> 07:13.846
MAN:
Can we ask you a few more questions?

07:14.016 --> 07:15.392
CAT:
Booster, wait.

07:15.560 --> 07:17.676
What an ass.

07:19.021 --> 07:20.397
You mean asset.

07:20.565 --> 07:23.682
-What?
-You wanted me to believe in heroes.

07:23.860 --> 07:25.441
Well, I think I finally might.

07:25.862 --> 07:27.523
He isn't hiding anything.

07:27.697 --> 07:29.858
You can see his face. His name--

07:30.032 --> 07:31.408
ls Booster Gold.

07:31.742 --> 07:36.111
Booster Gold could be
the city's answer to inspiration...

07:36.289 --> 07:38.655
...and my answer to that promotion.

07:40.293 --> 07:42.124
You're up for my promotion?

07:42.295 --> 07:43.910
It isn't yours just yet.

07:44.088 --> 07:48.252
And thanks to my reporting on the VRA,
l've gathered a small but vocal fan base.

07:48.426 --> 07:51.384
You should read their tweets.
They love me.

07:51.554 --> 07:55.388
Enough to convince the powers-that—be
to put my hat in the ring for that desk.

07:55.558 --> 07:57.094
May the best reporter win.

08:00.396 --> 08:02.728
Cat Grant, like nails on a chalkboard.

08:02.899 --> 08:05.436
She's not as bad as he is.

08:05.735 --> 08:09.728
Booster Gold's star will burn out faster
than you can say, "Up, up, and away."

08:09.906 --> 08:11.737
Let's focus on what's important here.

08:11.908 --> 08:13.398
And what is that, Lois?

08:13.701 --> 08:17.068
Unmaking Clark Kent
so that we can get the Blur out there.

08:20.917 --> 08:23.784
[CHATTERING]

08:31.385 --> 08:34.343
[GRUNTS & CROWD LAUGHS]

08:43.314 --> 08:45.145
Here, Jaime.

08:53.783 --> 08:54.943
Thanks, Dora.

08:58.287 --> 09:00.278
[CROWD LAUGHS]

09:00.456 --> 09:03.789
Sorry. I forgot I dropped it.

09:07.797 --> 09:08.786
[SIGHS]

09:18.766 --> 09:19.972
LOIS:
That's it.

09:22.478 --> 09:24.059
What does it say this time?

09:24.480 --> 09:26.766
"Kick me." A classic.

09:27.483 --> 09:28.643
I've had worse.

09:28.818 --> 09:29.978
Listen, kid.

09:30.152 --> 09:32.814
You should stand up for yourself.

09:33.406 --> 09:39.493
Don't slouch, talk with confidence,
and stop being so shy.

09:39.787 --> 09:42.028
It's okay to get mad.

09:43.708 --> 09:45.323
I guess so.

09:46.168 --> 09:47.829
Now, you go back over there...

09:48.004 --> 09:52.998
...you tell them you're mad as hell
and you're not gonna take it anymore.

09:56.679 --> 09:58.920
Oh, just try it with me.

09:59.390 --> 10:03.850
l'm-- I'm mad as hell
and I'm not gonna take it anymore.

10:04.020 --> 10:05.510
Okay.

10:05.688 --> 10:08.350
Now, like, punish them with it,
you know? Just--

10:08.524 --> 10:11.106
I'm mad as hell
and I'm not gonna take it anymore.

10:11.319 --> 10:13.184
Okay, look, it's eat or be eaten.

10:13.362 --> 10:15.694
So you get over there
and enjoy your meal, right?

10:15.865 --> 10:17.605
Go ahead.

10:51.067 --> 10:52.227
[SIGHS]

10:52.401 --> 10:54.653
Maybe he'll grow out of it.

10:58.824 --> 11:00.985
[CHITTERING]

11:08.918 --> 11:11.409
[SCREAMING]

11:17.802 --> 11:20.418
Oh, what's happening to me?

11:26.560 --> 11:29.267
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING
ON SPEAKERS]

11:31.190 --> 11:35.399
Have you or a loved one felt like you
needed help from someone who cares?

11:35.569 --> 11:39.027
Are you sick of all those masked men
blurring their way in and out...

11:39.198 --> 11:41.280
...without so much as a hello
orgoodbye?

11:41.450 --> 11:46.114
Well, don't settle for anything less than
the gold standard, as in Booster Gold.

11:46.288 --> 11:47.789
WOMEN [IN UNISON]:
Booster Gold.

11:48.708 --> 11:50.573
LOIS:
I appreciate the thought, but stop it.

11:50.751 --> 11:53.128
The all-new Clark
would not be sending me roses.

11:53.295 --> 11:55.957
-He's allergic to them, remember?
-I didn't send these.

12:01.429 --> 12:03.795
-Booster.
-Ew.

12:05.558 --> 12:08.971
Okay, Romeo will take the hint
soon enough and lose interest.

12:11.689 --> 12:14.772
-But you're obviously not.
-Did you know in the last 24 hours...

12:14.942 --> 12:17.979
...Booster Gold has made it
to every accident and crime scene?

12:18.195 --> 12:22.188
Okay, not to ask the obvious, but what's
wrong with having another hero in town?

12:22.616 --> 12:26.234
I mean,
aside from his ridiculous personality.

12:26.787 --> 12:29.779
If I didn't know better,
I'd say you were jealous of this guy.

12:29.957 --> 12:31.163
Jealous?

12:31.333 --> 12:32.994
Me?

12:33.210 --> 12:36.828
No. Lois, he seems to know when and
where these things are gonna happen.

12:37.006 --> 12:39.338
He doesn't stop the accident.
He just sweeps in.

12:39.508 --> 12:41.248
He makes the save, gets the photo-op.

12:41.427 --> 12:42.667
Okay, so drama sells.

12:42.845 --> 12:45.507
So do ratings.
He's on every single station.

12:45.681 --> 12:48.764
But if people find out that
he's doing this for personal fame...

12:48.934 --> 12:51.425
...they'll lose faith in heroes
just like before.

12:51.604 --> 12:53.344
Booster is the least of our problems.

12:53.522 --> 12:56.514
I've never been comfortable
in a suit and tie.

12:56.692 --> 12:58.193
I'm more at home in the lab.

12:58.360 --> 13:00.942
-Hey, I recognize him.
-|t's Ted Kord.

13:01.113 --> 13:03.195
-Kord Industries.
-Kord Industries.

13:03.365 --> 13:06.949
-That's why I founded Kord Industries.
-The Blackwater of the Midwest.

13:07.119 --> 13:11.533
High-tech device went missing when one
of his trucks crashed into Booster Gold.

13:11.957 --> 13:14.539
Kord claims that his company
is all about technology.

13:14.752 --> 13:17.334
Their research and development
includes many things...

13:17.505 --> 13:19.336
...not listed on their stock report.

13:19.507 --> 13:21.372
Like what?

13:23.010 --> 13:25.251
Disarming recovered super-weapons.

13:28.474 --> 13:31.682
Lois, I need to clean up Booster's mess
and find this missing tech.

13:31.852 --> 13:33.012
It could be dangerous.

13:38.734 --> 13:43.068
And I'll see what I can uncover
about our gold-plated glory hound.

13:45.658 --> 13:47.319
Thanks for being my number-one fan.

13:47.827 --> 13:49.067
Thank you.

13:50.412 --> 13:53.028
BOOSTER:
Thanks for being my number-one fan.

13:53.791 --> 13:56.282
Thanks for being my number-one fan.

13:59.547 --> 14:01.538
Awesome. Hello.

14:01.715 --> 14:03.251
Cat Grant of the Daily Planet.

14:03.425 --> 14:05.381
Well, thanks
for being my number-one fan.

14:05.553 --> 14:09.171
| find it so refreshing that one hero
doesn't have anything to hide.

14:09.807 --> 14:12.423
I mean, who would wanna hide
that face? Heh.

14:12.601 --> 14:13.977
[CHUCKLES]

14:14.311 --> 14:16.393
Did you have something
for me to sign?

14:18.941 --> 14:21.102
You're hoping to be interviewed
by Lois Lane--

14:21.277 --> 14:25.236
Sorry, blondie. Not interested.
It's gotta be Lois Lane or nobody.

14:25.406 --> 14:28.569
You may have people waiting,
but don't put yourself on a pedestal.

14:28.951 --> 14:31.909
You want a fan base bigger
than the Blur? I can do that.

14:32.079 --> 14:34.286
l have a following of my own,
you know.

14:34.915 --> 14:37.247
SKEETS: Sir, you have a message
from Miss Lane.

14:37.418 --> 14:38.624
[BOOSTER CLEARS THROAT]

14:40.045 --> 14:41.421
Did she get the flowers?

14:41.589 --> 14:42.920
They were signed for, sir.

14:43.090 --> 14:44.955
And apparently, they worked.

14:45.134 --> 14:49.093
Her interview made you-know-who
the hero of Metropolis.

14:49.263 --> 14:51.379
Not if I get there first
this time around.

14:54.393 --> 14:57.556
I should've come back a long time ago.
Where does she wanna meet?

14:58.272 --> 15:01.560
Actually, she's closing in on you now.

15:06.488 --> 15:09.070
Sir, um, excuse me. Oh--

15:09.742 --> 15:11.573
Miss Lane.

15:12.244 --> 15:14.986
Your endorsement is gonna take me
right to the top.

15:15.164 --> 15:18.907
I didn't come here to endorse you.
I came here to tell you to hit the skies.

15:19.418 --> 15:21.500
Metropolis is the Blur's jurisdiction.

15:23.005 --> 15:25.166
-ls it?
-Yeah.

15:25.341 --> 15:27.673
That's funny. That's not
what these people are saying. Hey.

15:27.843 --> 15:28.923
[CROWD CHEERS]

15:29.094 --> 15:31.631
See, perception is reality, Miss Lane.

15:31.805 --> 15:34.182
Look at the reality that I've created.

15:34.350 --> 15:38.013
People are excited about a hero
that they can actually see.

15:38.354 --> 15:40.515
LOIS: Mm.
-They wanna look up in the sky.

15:40.689 --> 15:43.146
They need to look up in the sky.

15:43.317 --> 15:46.150
The Blur, pfft, isjust not giving it to them.

15:46.320 --> 15:49.187
But me,
I am delivering the goods, baby.

15:49.365 --> 15:51.276
Heroism is not for sale.

15:51.450 --> 15:53.532
Oh, everything's for sale...

15:53.702 --> 15:55.442
...if not for rent.

15:55.621 --> 15:58.863
And that's why you'll never be
anything like the Blur.

15:59.041 --> 16:01.123
You just don't get it, do you, gorgeous?

16:01.293 --> 16:02.794
Apparently not.

16:03.545 --> 16:07.288
I didn't come here to be like the Blur.

16:07.466 --> 16:09.673
I came here to replace him.

16:12.846 --> 16:14.302
That'll never happen.

16:16.350 --> 16:17.681
Thank you.

16:22.439 --> 16:24.896
SKEETS: Are you sure trying
to usurp Clark Kent’s destiny...

16:25.067 --> 16:27.934
...for your own is a wise decision?

16:28.737 --> 16:31.353
Greatest hero on Earth. Oh.

16:31.532 --> 16:34.569
Skeets, that's a pretty good
job description.

16:34.743 --> 16:39.703
-But, sir--
-Skeets, what other choice do I have?

16:39.873 --> 16:44.708
After all that's happened, this is my
last chance to be somebody again...

16:48.716 --> 16:53.585
...by grabbing Clark Kent's place
in history.

16:55.597 --> 16:57.724
[SCREAMING AND CHEERING]

17:14.867 --> 17:16.027
I saw him first.

17:16.493 --> 17:18.029
Who?

17:18.203 --> 17:20.535
Who else? Booster Gold.

17:20.706 --> 17:23.994
You're competitive, but you can't
just sweep in and take my story.

17:24.168 --> 17:26.159
You didn't want anything to do
with him.

17:26.503 --> 17:29.370
I don't wanna have anything to do
with him...

17:29.715 --> 17:31.330
.uoryou.

17:32.301 --> 17:34.041
Booster's more real than the Blur.

17:34.803 --> 17:36.885
How many times have we seen
the Blur's face?

17:37.056 --> 17:40.139
How many times has the Blur told us
why he's protecting us?

17:40.768 --> 17:43.350
It's not for a paycheck, Cat.

17:44.021 --> 17:46.979
And real heroes don't stop
to strike a pose.

17:47.149 --> 17:49.140
Real heroes don't have anything
to hide.

17:49.318 --> 17:51.900
The Blur has reasons
for every single thing he does.

17:52.071 --> 17:53.732
So does Booster Gold.

17:55.240 --> 17:59.279
You keep backing your horse, Lois,
and I'll back mine.

18:06.043 --> 18:08.159
KORD:
We can't replace what's been lost, Sonia.

18:08.337 --> 18:12.080
Send out the entire field team. We're
not leaving Metropolis until we find it.

18:12.257 --> 18:13.667
CLARK:
Excuse me, Mr. Kord.

18:13.842 --> 18:15.423
Who are you?

18:16.303 --> 18:18.669
Clark Kent, Daily-- Daily Planet.

18:18.847 --> 18:21.805
Press? Listen, I'm only giving
statements, no interviews.

18:22.101 --> 18:24.308
How'd you get through security?
Security.

18:24.478 --> 18:27.720
As one of the leading industrialists,
I know how busy you must be.

18:27.898 --> 18:30.890
This must be important
if you came all the way from Chicago...

18:31.068 --> 18:33.775
-...to lead up the lost and found.
-No comment.

18:36.949 --> 18:40.407
Sir, how important is this weapon?
How dangerous is it?

18:42.246 --> 18:44.077
Who said we were
looking for a weapon?

18:46.542 --> 18:50.160
-What's your name again?
-Kent. Clark-- Clark Kent. I'm sorry.

18:50.337 --> 18:54.706
I work for the Daily Planet.
Well, we already went over that.

18:54.883 --> 18:58.671
I'm a reporter, but I'm not
a front-page reporter, though.

18:58.846 --> 19:04.011
I sit next to someone who told me you
used to work for the government and, uh....

19:04.977 --> 19:08.811
Is there a restroom I could use here?
I had a milkshake on the way in and it....

19:09.731 --> 19:12.222
I trust you'll go out
the same way you came in.

19:14.361 --> 19:15.476
Thank you.

19:18.740 --> 19:21.447
I have Booster Gold on the line, sir.

19:24.329 --> 19:26.661
You can assure me you'll be discreet?

19:26.832 --> 19:30.040
This incident is drawing more attention
than / am comfortable with.

19:30.252 --> 19:32.994
BOOSTER: I'm happy to help you ﬁnd
your missing trinket, Mr. Kord.

19:33.172 --> 19:34.958
KORD:
It is not a trinket. It is a weapon.

19:35.132 --> 19:38.670
A very dangerous one,
especially to anyone who ﬁnds it.

19:38.844 --> 19:41.631
-You need to handle it with caution.
BOOSTER: I will.

19:41.805 --> 19:43.887
As soon as we make a deal.

19:44.600 --> 19:47.808
Well, I'm sure we can work out
some kind of a reward, Mr. Gold.

19:47.978 --> 19:49.889
BOOSTER:
I had something in mind.

19:50.063 --> 19:53.521
I know you and the mayor,
you're like peanut butter and jelly.

19:53.692 --> 19:56.934
You pull some strings,
get me the key to the city...

19:57.112 --> 19:59.899
...l’l/ help you ﬁnd
whatever you need me to ﬁnd.

20:00.073 --> 20:01.859
You want the key to the city?

20:02.034 --> 20:05.868
Let's just say it's the last thing
on my to-do list.

20:06.038 --> 20:07.824
So can you swing it or not?

20:10.209 --> 20:12.951
Whatever it takes
to get the scarab back.

20:32.648 --> 20:35.230
MAN 1: You ready over there?
MAN 2: Almost.

20:36.944 --> 20:38.024
MAN 1:
Drop it.

20:45.744 --> 20:47.484
Lois.

20:48.121 --> 20:50.203
ANNOUNCER [OVER PA]:
Take a shot in the dark.

20:50.749 --> 20:53.866
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING
ON SPEAKERS]

21:00.467 --> 21:02.048
BOOSTER:
All right. I like it, I like it.

21:02.219 --> 21:03.254
[MUSIC STOPS]

21:03.428 --> 21:06.545
I need a sound check. I wanna make sure
they can hear my speech.

21:06.723 --> 21:07.803
MAN 1 :
Take five, everybody.

21:07.975 --> 21:11.012
SKEETS: Will you be thanking anyone, sir?
-Me.

21:11.186 --> 21:12.892
And maybe my mom.

21:13.063 --> 21:15.145
People love that sentimental stuff.

21:15.357 --> 21:18.099
It scores pretty big with the ladies too.

21:20.195 --> 21:21.981
Booster Gold?

21:22.489 --> 21:24.696
Hey, a fan.

21:25.409 --> 21:27.445
I need your help.
Something happened to me.

21:27.619 --> 21:29.951
Look, if you need anything,
call the hotline.

21:30.122 --> 21:32.283
I tried. They said you were here.

21:33.500 --> 21:36.958
I am here, but I'm kind of busy. Ha, ha.

21:37.713 --> 21:39.874
But I don't know what to do.

21:40.924 --> 21:42.164
It....

21:42.384 --> 21:43.624
It attacked me.

21:43.802 --> 21:45.087
It's all right. Here.

21:45.262 --> 21:48.004
Listen, I'll make sure they pencil you in.
All right?

21:48.181 --> 21:50.217
You look all right to me.

21:52.144 --> 21:53.554
I'm not all right at all.

21:53.729 --> 21:55.970
BOOSTER:
Okay. Ladies.

21:56.148 --> 21:59.311
-Who wants to be the star of the show?
ALL: Me.

21:59.484 --> 22:04.274
Just kidding. I'm the star of the show.
You're gonna wave, you'll smile...

22:04.448 --> 22:07.030
...but I need somebody to hand me
the key to the city.

22:07.200 --> 22:09.031
-Who's that gonna be?
CAT: Me.

22:12.831 --> 22:14.662
I'll do it.

22:16.418 --> 22:18.158
Yeah.

22:18.545 --> 22:20.501
You sure will.

22:24.468 --> 22:27.801
[CHITTERING]

22:29.765 --> 22:33.428
No. No!

22:39.483 --> 22:40.939
Destroy.

22:53.330 --> 22:55.366
-What? What is it, Clark?
-The billboard.

22:55.749 --> 22:58.707
-Yes, they put them up already.
-Lois, what are you doing?

22:58.877 --> 23:00.959
I had a run-in
with our gloating guardian...

23:01.129 --> 23:04.963
...and he actually thinks
he can replace you.

23:05.384 --> 23:08.046
I appreciate the support,
but this is not a competition.

23:08.220 --> 23:10.176
I'm not gonna let the Blur be forgotten...

23:10.347 --> 23:12.679
...because some shiny object
flies up into the sky.

23:12.849 --> 23:16.933
Booster is not the bright and shiny object
we need to be worried about.

23:20.190 --> 23:21.930
What is this? A bug?

23:22.150 --> 23:24.641
That's what Ted Kord is looking for.

23:24.820 --> 23:26.902
Ichecked.
It's extraterrestrial technology.

23:27.072 --> 23:28.778
When they brought this scarab in...

23:28.949 --> 23:31.907
...it bonded with Kord's scientist
like it was a parasite.

23:32.077 --> 23:33.817
The guy's name was Dan Garrett.

23:35.372 --> 23:38.660
He and the scarab merged as one.

23:39.251 --> 23:42.618
Garrett killed three people
and died when they tried to take it off.

23:42.796 --> 23:44.957
-This thing is somewhere in Metropolis?
-Yeah.

23:45.173 --> 23:48.916
Kord hired Booster to bring it back
in exchange for the key to the city.

23:49.094 --> 23:51.460
Your key to the city.
He's been here like a day.

23:51.680 --> 23:55.172
I mean, if there was ever a time
for the Blur to debut his dashing smile--

23:55.350 --> 23:56.886
You know I can't do that yet.

23:57.060 --> 24:01.520
No, not until we've reverse-Pygmalioned
this serious stud into a blunder of beige.

24:02.482 --> 24:06.191
Still, I'd love to see you boost our
golden boy up into the stratosphere.

24:06.361 --> 24:07.396
Well....

24:07.571 --> 24:09.186
[CELL PHONE BEEPING]

24:12.701 --> 24:14.282
Speak of the showboat.

24:16.830 --> 24:17.910
Booster.

24:18.081 --> 24:20.322
BOOSTER:
Hey, Blur boy.

24:20.625 --> 24:22.286
I mean, Clark.

24:22.711 --> 24:25.498
I saw the sign. Touche.

24:25.714 --> 24:28.171
I was calling Lois
to thank her for the photo-op.

24:28.341 --> 24:30.957
We need to get together
and find Kord's weapon.

24:31.136 --> 24:32.251
It's dangerous.

24:32.429 --> 24:35.045
Danger. It's my middle name.

24:35.223 --> 24:37.680
So is fame, fortune and front page,
Clark.

24:37.851 --> 24:39.307
We need to talk.

24:41.396 --> 24:43.136
Now.

24:43.398 --> 24:44.979
Fine.

24:45.567 --> 24:49.401
But first-- I mean, can you smell it?
That's impending fame.

24:49.571 --> 24:51.527
It's true
what they say about Metropolis.

24:51.740 --> 24:53.401
I mean, it has everything.

24:53.575 --> 24:56.282
Except somebody to look up to.

24:56.745 --> 24:57.860
And that's you?

24:58.038 --> 25:00.324
It's gonna be me. Yeah.

25:00.499 --> 25:02.364
You save people for profit, for fame...

25:02.542 --> 25:06.660
...while the real heroes, they're out there
earning back the people's trust.

25:06.838 --> 25:11.081
-You're putting me and my friends at risk.
-No one's at risk, all right?

25:11.259 --> 25:15.468
Not as long as I keep flying in,
whoosh, for that heroic rescue.

25:16.681 --> 25:20.890
Legion ring. You're from the future?
You're a Legionnaire?

25:21.061 --> 25:23.052
Not exactly.

25:23.396 --> 25:25.478
But they're really good friends of mine.

25:25.649 --> 25:27.856
Ah, they're more like acquaintances,
actually.

25:28.026 --> 25:30.688
-You stole that ring.
-I borrowed the ring.

25:30.862 --> 25:34.320
But like the legion, yes,
I'm from the future, Clark.

25:34.783 --> 25:38.116
And I always know exactly what to do
at exactly the right time...

25:38.286 --> 25:42.154
...thanks to the assistance
of my historical data droid.

25:42.332 --> 25:43.412
Say hello, Skeets.

25:43.583 --> 25:45.244
SKEETS:
Pleasure to meet you, Mr. Kent.

25:45.418 --> 25:47.409
Time travel's nothing
to play around with.

25:47.587 --> 25:49.578
You've already changed history...

25:49.798 --> 25:53.416
...and I doubt that Skeets has any record
of what happened to Kord's scarab.

25:53.927 --> 25:55.758
-Negative, sir.
-It doesn't matter.

25:55.929 --> 25:58.090
I can handle whatever comes
around the corner.

25:58.306 --> 26:01.719
Listen, you're talking to the single
greatest hero of the 25th century.

26:01.893 --> 26:03.679
I'm worshiped by billions.

26:04.396 --> 26:05.852
I'm kind of a big deal.

26:06.022 --> 26:07.307
Until someone gets hurt.

26:07.482 --> 26:09.063
It's not gonna happen.

26:09.234 --> 26:10.644
Trust me.

26:10.819 --> 26:12.650
Besides...

26:12.821 --> 26:15.028
...I know what this is really about.

26:15.198 --> 26:19.316
You can't stand the fact that people
are choosing me over you, right?

26:19.828 --> 26:21.910
I understand. I get it.

26:22.080 --> 26:24.321
You want the glory, don't you?

26:25.000 --> 26:27.582
I'm gonna give you your chance
to claim it.

26:29.588 --> 26:32.330
Right through here,
I'm about to get the key to the city.

26:32.757 --> 26:38.468
And history says whoever gets the key
becomes this city's man of steel.

26:38.888 --> 26:39.968
Or gold.

26:41.933 --> 26:44.140
All you gotta do is show me up.

26:44.769 --> 26:46.225
Reveal yourself to the world.

26:46.396 --> 26:50.139
Put that suit on display
and steal my thunder. What do you say?

26:50.942 --> 26:52.978
The suit doesn't make the hero.

26:53.153 --> 26:55.986
A hero's made in the moment
by the choices that he makes...

26:56.156 --> 26:58.147
...and the reasons that he makes them.

26:58.742 --> 27:01.609
A hero brings out the best in people.

27:03.163 --> 27:06.451
I don't doubt that behind that star,
there is a hero...

27:06.625 --> 27:08.536
...but I haven't seen him.

27:08.710 --> 27:10.041
Not yet.

27:15.050 --> 27:19.089
I knew you wouldn't have the cajones
to smile for the camera, Clark. I knew it.

27:22.182 --> 27:23.513
SKEETS:
They're ready for you, Sir.

27:23.683 --> 27:25.344
That's my cue.

27:28.813 --> 27:30.189
Oh, and, Clark...

27:30.940 --> 27:33.647
...hang up the glasses
and the red-and-blue suit.

27:33.818 --> 27:36.400
You're not gonna be needing them
anymore.

27:37.489 --> 27:39.775
The world has me now.

27:39.949 --> 27:41.075
[CHUCKLES]

27:50.001 --> 27:51.411
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING
ON SPEAKERS]

27:51.586 --> 27:55.374
Take a Shot in the dark
Take a Shot in the dark

27:58.843 --> 28:01.300
Okay, let's rehearse this one more time.

28:01.471 --> 28:04.634
Thank you, Mr. Mayor.
Thank you all for this opportunity...

28:04.808 --> 28:08.221
...to protect and serve
this great city of Metropolis.

28:08.436 --> 28:09.516
And then you would say:

28:09.688 --> 28:12.225
"Now me and my city
would like to thank you...

28:12.440 --> 28:14.146
...the powerful, the intelligent...

28:14.317 --> 28:20.187
...the humble Booster Gold."

28:20.532 --> 28:22.864
WOMAN:
Oh, my God. Oh!

28:23.034 --> 28:24.615
[PANTS]

28:30.208 --> 28:31.323
BLUE BEETLE:
Targeting.

28:31.626 --> 28:34.459
-Destroy.
-Don't. No.

28:40.218 --> 28:41.754
Stop. Stop.

28:46.516 --> 28:48.131
Don't.

28:57.318 --> 29:00.481
Skeets, this wasn't supposed to happen.
What's going on?

29:02.240 --> 29:03.320
Don't. No.

29:05.577 --> 29:08.364
SKEETS: l have no record of this
or our apparent attacker, Sir.

29:08.538 --> 29:10.620
It appears Clark Kent may be correct.

29:10.790 --> 29:14.032
Our presence here has made my
historical data somewhat inaccurate.

29:16.504 --> 29:17.710
I'm sorry.

29:19.007 --> 29:20.747
Booster.

29:20.925 --> 29:22.301
What are you gonna do?

29:23.178 --> 29:24.338
Okay.

29:28.099 --> 29:29.885
No. No.

29:34.898 --> 29:37.856
SKEETS: May I offer a piece of advice
from your former career, sir?

29:38.026 --> 29:39.106
Football?

29:39.277 --> 29:42.269
Go big or go home.

29:42.697 --> 29:44.688
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

29:47.535 --> 29:49.116
I'm sorry.

30:47.846 --> 30:49.211
The Blur.

30:51.391 --> 30:52.881
Hey.

30:54.143 --> 30:55.849
No. No.

30:59.107 --> 31:00.222
[YELLS]

31:06.865 --> 31:08.730
One move, bug...

31:08.908 --> 31:10.990
...I will zap you to honeybee heaven.

31:11.160 --> 31:14.152
I can't-- I can't do-- I can't do anything.

31:19.419 --> 31:22.161
[GROANS]

31:23.631 --> 31:25.417
Mr. Gold?

31:27.260 --> 31:29.421
-You're that kid.
-I can't control this suit.

31:29.637 --> 31:30.968
Please help me.

31:31.139 --> 31:33.972
Listen, kid,
I'm sorry I blew you off earlier.

31:36.728 --> 31:39.686
-You can help me. You're a hero.
-No, I'm not.

31:40.690 --> 31:43.306
Not like you think I am, kid.

31:43.735 --> 31:45.191
But, listen, you can be.

31:46.988 --> 31:51.778
Someone once told me that the suit
doesn't make the hero, so you fight it.

31:54.662 --> 31:56.869
I can't.

31:59.250 --> 32:01.206
Yes, you can. Fight it.

32:01.377 --> 32:03.083
You can be a hero.

32:03.796 --> 32:06.538
You just have to have faith
in what you are...

32:06.716 --> 32:08.047
...and what you're gonna be.

32:10.386 --> 32:12.843
It's your choice, kid.

32:13.014 --> 32:14.754
You choose.

32:15.266 --> 32:18.975
Okay. Okay. Okay.

32:20.688 --> 32:22.269
I can-- I can do this.

32:24.901 --> 32:26.937
Yeah, I can do this.

32:27.111 --> 32:28.317
I can-- I can do it.

32:28.488 --> 32:30.695
I can do it. I can do it.

32:45.213 --> 32:46.828
[YELLING]

32:56.516 --> 32:58.131
Kid...

32:58.476 --> 32:59.807
...you all right?

33:03.022 --> 33:06.230
-Yeah.
-All right.

33:08.486 --> 33:09.851
Oh. Whoa.

33:13.825 --> 33:14.905
Thanks.

33:17.954 --> 33:19.569
Yeah.

33:25.878 --> 33:27.789
It's all right.

33:39.934 --> 33:41.845
You surprised me.

33:42.270 --> 33:44.352
I surprised myself.

33:45.231 --> 33:48.598
But still, I screwed up, major.

33:48.776 --> 33:52.985
I thought if I did everything you did
or are going to do...

33:53.156 --> 33:55.238
...I'd take your spot in history.

33:56.784 --> 33:58.240
Question is, why?

33:58.786 --> 34:00.447
Why?

34:00.913 --> 34:03.450
I forget you've never felt it.

34:04.292 --> 34:07.910
The rush of being out there...

34:08.087 --> 34:11.579
...and being that miracle
that people are hoping for.

34:11.758 --> 34:16.593
Looking people in the eye and letting
them know, "You're gonna be safe."

34:19.015 --> 34:24.100
Oh, man, you never wanna
let that feeling end.

34:26.481 --> 34:29.644
That poor kid down there,
he took the brunt of my ego, Clark.

34:30.276 --> 34:33.643
I always knew all of this was gonna
blow up in my face sooner or later.

34:33.821 --> 34:35.106
I mean, it always does.

34:36.157 --> 34:41.652
The truth is, I am from the future,
but I'm no hero.

34:42.497 --> 34:46.206
I was a sports star
who started betting on his own games.

34:46.834 --> 34:49.325
And then I started throwing them.

34:52.006 --> 34:55.214
It was easier to lose than try to win.

34:57.804 --> 34:59.340
You still feel that way now?

34:59.680 --> 35:01.341
No.

35:01.682 --> 35:03.297
I don't.

35:04.143 --> 35:07.806
But the damage is done now.
I mean, in the future, I got caught.

35:07.980 --> 35:11.017
My fame, my fortune,
went right down the toilet...

35:11.192 --> 35:14.355
...along with my dignity
and my reputation and....

35:14.529 --> 35:17.066
You were right. I stole the ring.

35:17.240 --> 35:20.482
I stole the suit, even Skeets.

35:20.660 --> 35:22.821
SKEETS:
Afﬁrmative, sir.

35:23.579 --> 35:26.821
I came here to make a fresh start
and I made all the same mistakes.

35:27.708 --> 35:30.541
My own sister,
she said the exact same thing to me...

35:30.711 --> 35:33.043
...when my football career ended.

35:34.549 --> 35:37.712
She said,
"The suit doesn't make the hero."

35:39.554 --> 35:41.920
You helped Jaime break free
of that scarab.

35:42.098 --> 35:44.214
I was using your words.

35:44.392 --> 35:46.098
It doesn't matter.

35:46.269 --> 35:48.430
The fact is, in the moment,
you believed them.

35:48.604 --> 35:49.855
So did he.

35:51.899 --> 35:55.517
Look, I, uh.... I better get heading back.

35:55.695 --> 35:57.856
When you still have work to do here?

35:58.906 --> 36:01.943
Ted Kord agreed to remove the scarab.

36:02.118 --> 36:04.404
But Jaime will need someone
to watch over him.

36:05.746 --> 36:09.910
I know. It's not the front-page victory
you were looking for...

36:10.084 --> 36:11.745
...but it's an important one.

36:17.258 --> 36:18.589
[CHUCKLES]

36:18.759 --> 36:20.420
Yeah.

36:20.803 --> 36:22.509
Yeah.

36:24.599 --> 36:27.591
Well, you know what?
I got some advice for you too.

36:28.269 --> 36:29.759
What's that?

36:29.937 --> 36:32.599
The Blur. No, no, no.

36:32.773 --> 36:35.310
It sounds like a roller coaster
or something.

36:36.110 --> 36:38.601
You need something strong.
You need something simple.

36:38.779 --> 36:41.612
Something that actually starts
with that S you wear.

36:41.782 --> 36:43.522
Something...

36:44.118 --> 36:45.278
.usupen

36:46.954 --> 36:49.286
You gotta brand it, baby, you know?

36:50.750 --> 36:52.957
I'll start brainstorming.

36:54.045 --> 36:55.751
All right.

36:57.632 --> 36:59.748
Oh, Clark.

37:00.760 --> 37:02.796
You're an XL, right?

37:15.983 --> 37:17.974
This boy is absolutely unique.

37:18.152 --> 37:20.143
He managed to shut down the scarab.

37:20.696 --> 37:23.312
I'm guessing not everyone
has what it takes to do that.

37:24.825 --> 37:27.407
Does this mean you'll be able
to remove it from him?

37:27.578 --> 37:29.318
No.

37:30.164 --> 37:33.782
I mean, will that take away
the power it gives me?

37:35.127 --> 37:38.494
-Yes, but--
-I wanna learn how to use them.

37:39.632 --> 37:42.624
I wanna be a hero like Booster Gold.

37:43.386 --> 37:46.002
I don't know, kid, you know?

37:46.180 --> 37:51.971
What do you say we give Miss Lane here
an exclusive on the real hero of the day?

37:59.277 --> 38:00.687
Huh?

38:03.823 --> 38:06.314
Let's take this interview outside.

38:16.544 --> 38:18.660
Congratulations on the promotion, Lois.

38:22.341 --> 38:23.547
What's the catch?

38:23.718 --> 38:25.925
No catch. You deserved it.

38:28.180 --> 38:30.887
I guess I went a little too far
trying to compete.

38:31.058 --> 38:36.052
I so badly wanted to be the voice
of a hero too, that I nearly lost my head.

38:37.023 --> 38:39.514
Figuratively and literally.

38:39.692 --> 38:41.432
Thankfully, I didn't.

38:43.362 --> 38:45.353
You wanna know
how to be a great reporter?

38:46.699 --> 38:48.860
Do it your way.

38:49.035 --> 38:50.150
Be yourself.

38:55.708 --> 38:57.244
What's with the box? Moving on?

38:58.294 --> 39:00.910
Oh, moving in.

39:01.088 --> 39:04.421
You may be going upstairs, but I'll be
keeping cozy right down here.

39:04.592 --> 39:05.877
Just a few desks over.

39:06.927 --> 39:08.883
Is that the last of it, Lois?

39:09.930 --> 39:13.172
Clark, meet your new desk buddy.

39:13.684 --> 39:15.424
Really?

39:17.605 --> 39:18.811
I'm so sorry.

39:19.565 --> 39:25.936
Lois, Clark's nice and all, if you wanna
invest in a fixer-upper, but he's no Blur.

39:30.409 --> 39:31.615
No.

39:31.786 --> 39:33.322
No, he's not.

39:50.137 --> 39:54.426
After seeing all the trouble that Booster
went through, hiding his insecurities...

39:55.101 --> 39:57.308
...I think I can make the glasses work.

40:00.981 --> 40:04.314
-But--
-But what, Smallville? You owned it today.

40:04.485 --> 40:06.976
You went from sleek to geek
in under 24 hours.

40:07.154 --> 40:09.315
What could be wrong with that?

40:10.324 --> 40:12.861
I saw the way Cat looked at me.

40:14.286 --> 40:15.696
I also heard what she said.

40:15.871 --> 40:17.611
Yeah, and it's perfect.

40:17.998 --> 40:20.125
It's not perfect.

40:21.502 --> 40:23.868
Lois, it doesn't matter
what people say about me.

40:30.553 --> 40:32.509
This is about you.

40:33.973 --> 40:35.509
Me?

40:35.683 --> 40:38.220
You see, I can fly under the radar.

40:38.394 --> 40:40.555
I can live down expectations
of Clark Kent...

40:40.771 --> 40:43.513
...as long as the Blur's out there
saving people, but....

40:44.650 --> 40:45.685
But what?

40:48.988 --> 40:51.320
What are people gonna think about you?

40:52.533 --> 40:53.864
The strong...

40:55.202 --> 40:59.411
...and extremely sexy Lois Lane
wants to marry...

41:03.502 --> 41:05.208
...this new Clark Kent?

41:07.882 --> 41:11.215
How could they ever understand
that you'd be interested in this?

41:11.385 --> 41:14.047
Whoa, whoa, whoa, stop right there.

41:14.930 --> 41:18.218
Oh, trust me, Smallville.

41:18.893 --> 41:20.849
We can make this work.

41:25.316 --> 41:27.102
Oh, boy, can we.

42:11.946 --> 42:13.937
[English - US - SDH]
